<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1437,1432,1565]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1432,1457]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin adjective, “ 
<emphasis box="[668,789,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">macilentus</emphasis>
”, meaning thin, meagre, in reference to the extremely slender gena and to the narrow dark central stripe of frontal vitta bordered by golden tomentosity on the frontal vitta itself.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
